ZH: 1. 他的觉醒发生在年轻的时候。
EN: His awakening happened when he was young.

ZH: 2. 那次事件让她对社会的现实产生了觉醒。
EN: That event triggered her awakening to the realities of society.

ZH: 3. 要在生活中觉醒意味着要开始意识到自己的潜力。
EN: To awaken in life means to start recognizing one's potential.

ZH: 4. 她在学校里的觉醒是在大学期间。
EN: Her awakening in school happened during her college years.

ZH: 5. 觉醒需要勇气和决心。
EN: Awakening requires courage and determination.

ZH: 6. 这次旅行让我对自然界产生了深刻的觉醒。
EN: This trip has brought about a profound awakening to the natural world.

ZH: 7. 他的觉醒是逐渐发生的，不是一夜之间的事情。
EN: His awakening happened gradually, it wasn't an overnight thing.

ZH: 8. 这本书引起了我对自我成长的觉醒。
EN: This book sparked an awakening in me towards personal growth.

ZH: 9. 透过静坐，你能进入觉醒的状态。
EN: Through meditation, you can enter a state of awakening.

ZH: 10. 经历一场挫折后，他获得了觉醒。
EN: After experiencing a setback, he gained an awakening.

ZH: 11. 她对生活的觉醒让她重新审视自己的价值观。
EN: Her awakening to life made her reevaluate her values.

ZH: 12. 他的觉醒是在独处时发生的。
EN: His awakening happened when he was alone.

ZH: 13. 她的觉醒让她走上了自我发展的道路。
EN: Her awakening led her on the path of self-development.

ZH: 14. 觉醒是人类的一种进化过程。
EN: Awakening is a process of human evolution.

ZH: 15. 过去的错误让他获得了觉醒。
EN: Past mistakes led to his awakening.

ZH: 16. 觉醒是一种探索内在世界的过程。
EN: Awakening is a process of exploring the inner world.

ZH: 17. 他的觉醒带来了对心灵的平静。
EN: His awakening brought about a sense of peace to his soul.

ZH: 18. 经过一段时间的思考，他意识到这是他的觉醒时刻。
EN: After a period of reflection, he realized that this was his moment of awakening.

ZH: 19. 觉醒需要跨越自己的舒适区。
EN: Awakening requires stepping out of one's comfort zone.

ZH: 20. 她的觉醒是在经历人生困境后发生的。
EN: Her awakening happened after going through life's hardships.
